                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.30332/2605.30332v1/figures/teaser/sit/001310_tiger_ode.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Colored Noise Sampling (CNS). Samples from SiT-XL/2 on ImageNet-256 (with CFG) for different sampling strategies. While standard SDEs inject uniform white noise, our Colored Noise Sampling (CNS) dynamically reallocates injected stochastic energy to unresolved frequency bands. This actively leverages the network’s spectral bias to systematically steer the output toward the true data manifold, outperforming standard ODE and SDE solvers.",
